{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fa00d4e5-93a9-4f50-b8d9-865ba10173d9","content":"Yes, you'll hit **target framework compatibility issues**. MSTest v3 requires **.NET 6.0+** for .NET Core/.NET targets, while still supporting **.NET Framework 4.6.2+**.\n\nYour current targets and their status with MSTest v3:\n\n| Target | Status |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Not supported (EOL) |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Not supported (EOL) |\n\n**To migrate**, you'd need to update the unsupported targets to at least `net6.0` (or ideally `net8.0`). You'd also replace the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages with the unified `MSTest` meta-package:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.x.x\" />\n```\n\nWould you like me to update the project file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e83f3f8e-550e-4a0d-b744-9ee1b5e0233b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is multi-targeting `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They want to migrate to MSTest v3. Let me think about what compatibility issues they might face.\n\nMSTest v3 (the `MSTest` meta-package starting from 3.x) has several important changes:\n\n1. **Minimum supported frameworks**: MSTest v3 dropped support for older target frameworks. Specifically:\n   - `netcoreapp3.1` is no longer supported (it's out of support from Microsoft)\n   - `net5.0` is also no longer supported (out of support)\n   - `net462` should still work since MSTest v3 supports .NET Framework 4.6.2 and above\n\nSo they'd need to upgrade both `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` to at least `net6.0` to use MSTest v3, while `net462` can remain as-is.","outputTokens":707,"requestId":"67CB:2636C7:318F514:36C097B:69FD50D2"},"id":"2dd320e9-8e2e-4fec-9858-51330eb59532","timestamp":"2026-05-08T02:56:32.226Z","parentId":"3dd075d7-a2ef-4713-8fb1-8d6123192039"}
